t decision\u2011making, and a positive crew atmosphere, which are especially vital for the sustained teamwork required on long\u2011distance flights. The communication difficulty is a concern, but the existing positive crew feedback suggests it may be manageable, whereas the interpersonal issues of the other candidates (uncooperative/grumpy, arrogance, poor criticism handling) appear more likely to degrade crew performance over many hours.\n**Open questions that could affect my view:**\n- Do any of us have information on Candidate\u202fC\u2019s calmness under pressure or specific examples of how his communication difficulty manifests in safety\u2011critical situations?\n- Are there any positive teamwork or communication details for Candidate\u202fB that might offset his uncooperative tendencies?\n- Any evidence of Candidate\u202fD\u2019s calmness under pressure or how his arrogance impacts crew interaction on long flights?\nI will tentatively vote for **Candidate\u202fC**, pending any additional evidence that clarifies the impact of his communication style or reveals stronger calm\u2011under\u2011pressure traits in the other candidates.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
